source.name: Estimates of April 1 Population Density by County  for Washington, 1900 to Present
source.description: Population density is measured in persons per square mile.  The land area measurement excludes lakes and other water areas within.  Adjusted/corrected federal census counts used as the numerator for years 2000 and 2010.  The 2001-2009 population density estimates were derived from OFM's April 1 intercensal population estimate series.
